The example for "How can I run long-running tasks without blocking the server?" seems kind of weird. Could it be that the last two lines should not be in the method "blocking_task()"? They don't seem to make any sense there. Also, should "blocking_task()" really belong to the Class "MyHandler"?
```python

    class MyHandler(FTPHandler):

        def on_file_received(self, file):
        """Called every time a file has been received"""

        def blocking_task():
            time.sleep(5)
            self.add_channel()

            self.del_channel()
            threading.Thread(target=blocking_task).start()

Documentation for MD5Handler is incorrect becuase it is not returning nothing on a fail...

even thought the example returns true or false in a manner you would expect it should return nothing, and raise an exception when it fails!

